        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@cosmicwimp]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/u/cosmicwimp">@cosmicwimp</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>I <strong>love</strong> Alan Garner’s books!<br>
As a kid, Weirdstone and the Moon of Gomrath were some of my favourites. As a young adult I really enjoyed the Owl Service. Red Shift sort of confused me but again it made a strong impression. I got Boneland when it came out and it’s a great adult sequel to Weirdstone and Gomrath.</p>
<p>The powerful psychogeometry at work in his tales of Alderley Edge made my surrounding countryside seem far more magical than Narnia or Middle Earth to me.</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/t/companion-adventures/793/39">Read full topic</a></p>
